<refnamediv>
  <refname>stg-float</refname>
  <refpurpose>Push patches to the top, even if applied</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv id="_synopsis">
<blockquote>
<literallayout><emphasis>stg</emphasis> float [--] &lt;patches&gt;
<emphasis>stg</emphasis> float -s &lt;series&gt;</literallayout>
</blockquote>
</refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1 id="_description">
<title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<simpara>Push a patch or a range of patches to the top even if applied. The
necessary pop and push operations will be performed to accomplish
this. The <emphasis>--series</emphasis> option can be used to rearrange the (top) patches
as specified by the given series file (or the standard input).</simpara>
</refsect1>
<refsect1 id="_options">
<title>OPTIONS</title>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
-s FILE
</term>
<term>
--series FILE
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
        Rearrange according to the series FILE.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
-k
</term>
<term>
--keep
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
        Keep the local changes.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</refsect1>
